00:38:26,871 --> 00:38:27,997
We know it's hard

533
00:38:28,105 --> 00:38:30,539
because wheels aren't really seen
as exciting technology,

534
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:32,040
even though they are the original.

535
00:38:32,143 --> 00:38:38,013
Well, technology is a glittering lure,

536
00:38:38,115 --> 00:38:40,310
but there's the rare occasion

537
00:38:40,418 --> 00:38:43,819
when the public can be engaged
on the level beyond flash,

538
00:38:43,921 --> 00:38:48,756
if they have a sentimental
bond with the product.

539
00:38:48,859 --> 00:38:53,091
My first job,
I was in house at a fur company

540
00:38:53,197 --> 00:38:56,928
with this old pro copyrighter,
a Greek named Teddy.

541
00:38:57,034 --> 00:39:02,973
And Teddy told me the most
important idea in advertising is "new. "

542
00:39:04,075 --> 00:39:05,736
Creates an itch.

543
00:39:05,843 --> 00:39:07,538
You simply put your product in there

544
00:39:07,645 --> 00:39:10,079
as a kind of... calamine lotion.

545
00:39:11,315 --> 00:39:16,514
He also talked about a deeper bond
with the product.

546
00:39:16,620 --> 00:39:18,952
Nostalgia.

547
00:39:19,056 --> 00:39:22,219
It's delicate...

548
00:39:22,326 --> 00:39:24,453
but potent.

549
00:39:24,562 --> 00:39:25,927
Sweetheart.

550
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:39,006
Teddy told me that in Greek,

551
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:44,605
nostalgia literally means
the pain from an old wound.

552
00:39:49,153 --> 00:39:51,781
It's a twinge in your heart

553
00:39:51,889 --> 00:39:55,290
far more powerful than memory alone.

554
00:39:57,762 --> 00:39:59,559
This device...

555
00:39:59,663 --> 00:40:02,689
isn't a space ship.

556
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:05,064
It's a time machine.

557
00:40:08,706 --> 00:40:12,073
It goes backwards, forwards.

558
00:40:17,114 --> 00:40:22,416
It takes us to a place
where we ache to go again.

559
00:40:28,526 --> 00:40:30,357
It's not called the Wheel.

560
00:40:31,929 --> 00:40:34,159
It's called the Carousel.

561
00:40:38,636 --> 00:40:42,936
It lets us travel the way a child travels.

562
00:40:44,475 --> 00:40:48,138
Around and around
and back home again...

563
00:40:52,550 --> 00:40:55,781
to a place where we know
we are loved.

564
00:41:30,988 --> 00:41:33,183
Good luck at your next meeting.

565
00:41:37,995 --> 00:41:40,190
Don, I have to warn you, I'm not alone.

566
00:41:40,297 --> 00:41:41,730
It was beautiful.

567
00:41:41,832 --> 00:41:44,357
<i>Congratulations, mein Kommandant.</i>

568
00:41:44,468 --> 00:41:45,765
They called from the lobby.

569
00:41:45,870 --> 00:41:48,600
They cancelled their other meetings,
including DDB.

570
00:41:48,706 --> 00:41:50,037
Not just a victory for us.

571
00:41:50,140 --> 00:41:51,266
It's a victory for civilization.

572
00:41:51,375 --> 00:41:53,673
There's also more celebrating.

573
00:41:53,777 --> 00:41:56,678
Mr. Campbell, here,
your father-in-law called.

574
00:41:56,780 --> 00:41:58,611
He'll be in before Christmas.

575
00:41:58,716 --> 00:42:00,547
I've got to get married.

576
00:42:01,852 --> 00:42:04,047
No, thank you. I'm good.

577
00:42:09,326 --> 00:42:10,224
Here's how.

578
00:42:10,327 --> 00:42:11,385
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

579
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:16,796
You know what, Pete?

580
00:42:16,901 --> 00:42:20,530
I've got a way for you
to turn this account into a home run.

581
00:42:20,638 --> 00:42:22,970
He's on a roll.

582
00:42:23,073 --> 00:42:24,438
Clearasil.

583
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:26,567
You know who buys that?

584
00:42:26,677 --> 00:42:28,406
Young girls.

585
00:42:28,512 --> 00:42:31,640
What a difference it makes in their lives
to be blemish-free.

586
00:42:31,749 --> 00:42:33,546
I believe it does.

587
00:42:33,651 --> 00:42:37,018
We have the perfect writer for that.

588
00:42:37,121 --> 00:42:38,588
Peggy Olsen.

589
00:42:40,024 --> 00:42:41,685
That's funny.

590
00:42:41,792 --> 00:42:45,228
Freddy Rumsen and I were both
very impressed with her insight.

591
00:42:45,329 --> 00:42:46,193
Freddy Rumsen.

592
00:42:46,297 --> 00:42:47,628
- If I can weigh in...
- No.

593
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:49,198
Come on. That Belle Jolie thing.

594
00:42:49,300 --> 00:42:51,325
Plus you should have seen her
in that booth yesterday.

595
00:42:51,435 --> 00:42:53,027
She was like Kinsey but with balls.

596
00:42:54,204 --> 00:42:55,728
Stop joking already, will you, Don?

597
00:42:55,839 --> 00:42:57,136
Excuse me?

598
00:42:57,241 --> 00:42:59,732
This is my father-in-law.

599
00:42:59,843 --> 00:43:01,538
He's expecting the very best.

600
00:43:01,645 --> 00:43:04,045
I'm expecting the very best,

601
00:43:04,148 --> 00:43:07,777
not some little girl who'll walk away.

602
00:43:07,885 --> 00:43:11,184
You'll have to give back
that copy of Ayn Rand.

603
00:43:11,288 --> 00:43:13,313
Do you know how hard I worked
to get this account?

604
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:14,516
Who the hell is she?

605
00:43:14,625 --> 00:43:16,456
Peggy is not even a copywriter.

606
00:43:16,560 --> 00:43:17,618
She's a... a secretary.

607
00:43:17,728 --> 00:43:18,695
Peggy!

608
00:43:18,796 --> 00:43:20,457
Yes, Mr. Draper?

609
00:43:20,564 --> 00:43:24,625
Miss Olsen, you are now a junior copywriter.

610
00:43:24,735 --> 00:43:29,297
Your first account will be delivering
Clearasil to the spotted masses.

611
00:43:29,406 --> 00:43:30,532
What?

612
00:43:30,641 --> 00:43:32,302
Don't act surprised.

613
00:43:32,409 --> 00:43:34,809
Is this really happening?

614
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:37,840
Yes, it is.

615
00:43:39,350 --> 00:43:40,647
My goodness.

616
00:43:42,886 --> 00:43:45,821
I will do my sincere best.

617
00:43:48,025 --> 00:43:49,652
Good to hear.

618
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:53,491
Mr. Campbell, here,
will brief you after the holiday.

619
00:43:57,101 --> 00:43:59,763
Of course.

620
00:43:59,870 --> 00:44:01,462
That'll be all.

621
00:44:01,572 --> 00:44:04,336
Thank you, Mr. Draper.

622
00:44:08,912 --> 00:44:11,847
I said congratulations, didn't I?

623
00:44:11,949 --> 00:44:14,645
Although sometimes when
people get what they want,

624
00:44:14,752 --> 00:44:16,947
they realize how limited
their goals were.

625
00:44:17,054 --> 00:44:19,352
So I guess I'll put you
in with Victor Manning.

626
00:44:19,456 --> 00:44:21,356
David Steuben got fired.

627
00:44:21,458 --> 00:44:22,720
Fired?

628
00:44:22,826 --> 00:44:24,293
People hated his work.

629
00:44:25,562 --> 00:44:26,893
Will I get business cards?

630
00:44:28,732 --> 00:44:31,257
Please make all your
requests through Bridget.

631
00:44:31,368 --> 00:44:32,300
Of course.

632
00:44:32,403 --> 00:44:33,961
Peggy, I know you a little.

633
00:44:34,071 --> 00:44:36,665
Remember, just because
you now have a door,

634
00:44:36,774 --> 00:44:38,969
don't forget that once you didn't.

635
00:44:39,076 --> 00:44:41,840
Think of the other girls,
or they won't think of you.

636
00:44:44,214 --> 00:44:46,705
Vic Manning, I'd like you
to meet Peggy Olsen.

637
00:44:46,817 --> 00:44:48,148
She'll be taking Mr. Steuben's desk.

638
00:44:48,252 --> 00:44:49,651
Nice to meet you.

639
00:44:51,388 --> 00:44:53,288
I don't feel so swell.

640
00:44:53,390 --> 00:44:54,982
I think I should go home.

641
00:44:55,092 --> 00:44:57,959
I have to stop eating off the cart.

642
00:44:58,062 --> 00:45:00,030
If you're trying to find
a way to go out and celebrate,

643
00:45:00,130 --> 00:45:01,597
you should ask your secretary
to cover for you.

644
00:45:01,699 --> 00:45:02,927
Very funny.

645
00:45:04,368 --> 00:45:06,063
Happy Thanksgiving.

646
00:45:06,170 --> 00:45:07,159
You, too, Joan.

647
00:45:07,271 --> 00:45:09,535
David and I had a deal.

648
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:11,232
No meetings in here, okay?

649
00:45:11,341 --> 00:45:12,399
And no music.

650
00:45:27,057 --> 00:45:28,684
What can we do for you today?

651
00:45:28,792 --> 00:45:31,454
My stomach hurts really bad.

652
00:45:31,562 --> 00:45:34,258
I think I had a bad sandwich.

653
00:45:34,364 --> 00:45:36,229
Let's take a look.

654
00:45:44,641 --> 00:45:46,108
Oh, my God.

655
00:45:46,210 --> 00:45:50,647
Honey, you didn't mention
that you were expecting.

656
00:45:50,748 --> 00:45:52,443
What?

657
00:45:52,549 --> 00:45:54,278
You're going to be a mother.

658
00:45:58,055 --> 00:45:59,317
That's impossible.

659
00:45:59,423 --> 00:46:02,950
You want us to call your husband
or your boyfriend?

660
00:46:05,395 --> 00:46:06,589
I don't understand.

661
00:46:06,697 --> 00:46:08,130
Stop talking.

662
00:46:11,468 --> 00:46:14,096
Now listen, we're going
to get you up to Maternity.

663
00:46:14,204 --> 00:46:17,605
No. No, that's not possible.

664
00:46:24,715 --> 00:46:26,114
Do you feel that?

665
00:46:39,630 --> 00:46:40,688
My God!

666
00:46:40,798 --> 00:46:42,095
We need a wheelchair.

667
00:46:42,199 --> 00:46:43,598
It hurts!

668
00:46:43,700 --> 00:46:45,565
It's going to be okay, all right?

669
00:46:45,669 --> 00:46:47,227
We just want you to calm down.

670
00:46:47,337 --> 00:46:48,235
You don't understand.

671
00:46:48,338 --> 00:46:50,169
We need a wheelchair!

672
00:46:53,477 --> 00:46:56,310
Call Dr. Wilson in Psychiatry.

673
00:47:06,390 --> 00:47:08,381
Oh.

674
00:47:08,492 --> 00:47:10,153
Hello, darling.

675
00:47:15,365 --> 00:47:17,560
Oh, were they having
a party at the office?

676
00:47:17,668 --> 00:47:18,692
Yes.

677
00:47:20,337 --> 00:47:22,237
I think I should...

678
00:47:22,339 --> 00:47:23,772
lie down.

679
00:47:23,874 --> 00:47:26,434
That's a good idea.

680
00:47:26,543 --> 00:47:28,602
Sure. Rest up.

681
00:47:28,712 --> 00:47:30,805
But make sure you're awake later.

682
00:47:30,914 --> 00:47:32,541
Daddy!

683
00:47:57,875 --> 00:48:00,776
Would you like to try to feed him?

684
00:48:04,181 --> 00:48:06,649
Don't you want
to hold him, sweetheart?

685
00:48:55,499 --> 00:48:57,091
Hello?

686
00:48:57,200 --> 00:48:59,031
Don?

687
00:49:06,376 --> 00:49:07,809
What are you doing here?

688
00:49:07,911 --> 00:49:10,277
Daddy! Are you coming with us?

689
00:49:10,380 --> 00:49:13,781
No, he isn't. Daddy has to work.

690
00:49:13,884 --> 00:49:15,749
But you can drive us
to the station.

691
00:49:15,852 --> 00:49:17,217
I haven't called the taxi yet.

692
00:49:17,321 --> 00:49:18,788
I'm coming with you.

693
00:49:20,757 --> 00:49:23,055
Really?

694
00:49:23,160 --> 00:49:25,025
You are?

695
00:49:25,128 --> 00:49:26,652
I'll pack the car.

696
00:49:26,763 --> 00:49:28,355
We'll be there before midnight.

697
00:49:35,772 --> 00:49:36,761
Daddy's coming with you.

698
00:49:36,873 --> 00:49:37,771
- Daddy!
- Daddy!

699
00:49:40,344 --> 00:49:42,369
Oh, my goodness.

700
00:49:50,854 --> 00:49:51,946
Hello?

701
00:49:55,459 --> 00:49:56,687
Hello.
